<p><b>Raytheon Company</b> (<a href="/wiki/New_York_Stock_Exchange" title="New York Stock Exchange">NYSE</a>:&#160;<a href="http://www.nyse.com/about/listed/rtn.html" class="external text" title="http://www.nyse.com/about/listed/rtn.html" rel="nofollow">RTN</a>) is a major <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Defense_contractor" title="Defense contractor">defense contractor</a> and industrial corporation with core <a href="/wiki/Manufacturing" title="Manufacturing">manufacturing</a> concentrations in <a href="/wiki/Defense_systems" title="Defense systems" class="mw-redirect">defense systems</a> and defense and commercial <a href="/wiki/Electronics" title="Electronics">electronics</a>. It was previously involved in corporate and special-mission <a href="/wiki/Aircraft" title="Aircraft">aircraft</a> until early 2007. Raytheon is the world's largest producer of guided missiles.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Established in 1922, the company <a href="/wiki/Incorporation_(business)" title="Incorporation (business)">reincorporated</a> in 1928 and adopted its present name in 1959. The company has around 73,000 employees worldwide and annual revenues of approximately <a href="/wiki/US$" title="US$" class="mw-redirect">US$</a>20 billion. More than 90 percent of Raytheon's revenues were obtained from defense contracts and, as of 2007, it was the fifth largest defense contractor in the world,<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> and is the fourth largest <a href="/wiki/List_of_United_States_defense_contractors" title="List of United States defense contractors">defense contractor in the United States</a> by <a href="/wiki/Revenue" title="Revenue">revenue</a>.</p>
<p>Raytheon Headquarters was moved from <a href="/wiki/Lexington,_Massachusetts" title="Lexington, Massachusetts">Lexington, Massachusetts</a> to <a href="/wiki/Waltham,_Massachusetts" title="Waltham, Massachusetts">Waltham, Massachusetts</a> on October 27, 2003.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3" title=""><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup> The company was previously headquartered in Waltham from 1941 until it opened its then Lexington headquarters in 1961.</p>
